    <h1 class="cs-h2 cs-h2--display">Scaling a Provider Platform Without Scaling Complexity</h1>
    <p class="cs-hero-sub cs-hero-sub--wide">Over three years as BookYourPet&rsquo;s sole product designer, I evolved a tightly coupled provider platform across service setup, team operations, booking, and subscription &mdash; reducing how much of the system businesses had to understand upfront.</p>

    <div class="cs-divider-grid cs-divider-grid--hero">
      <div>
        <div class="cs-label">PLATFORM RESTRUCTURING</div>
        <div class="cs-stat-value">4 <span class="cs-stat-annotation">dependencies moved out of service setup</span></div>
        <div class="cs-stat-label">Location &middot; staff eligibility &middot; capacity &middot; universal alerts</div>
        <div class="cs-stat-note">Shared, derived, and team-owned decisions moved out of individual service setup.</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="cs-label">ONBOARDING SIMPLIFICATION</div>
        <div class="cs-stat-value">6 <span class="cs-stat-annotation">steps</span> <span class="accent">&rarr;</span> 3 <span class="cs-stat-annotation">primary stages</span></div>
        <div class="cs-stat-label">Account &middot; business essentials &middot; subscription</div>
        <div class="cs-stat-note">Reduced how much businesses had to configure before entering the product.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cs-divider-grid cs-divider-grid--tight cs-divider-grid--bleed">
      <div>
        <div class="cs-label">ROLE</div>
        <div class="cs-text">Sole product designer across a three-year platform evolution</div>
      </div>
